---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config/site";
---

<MainLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about AI Kit Guides — our mission, our team, and why we created this blog to help you navigate the world of AI tools."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-ink-900 mb-6">About AI Kit Guides</h1>

    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        AI Kit Guides was created with one simple goal: to help everyday people navigate the rapidly evolving world of AI tools. The AI landscape moves fast — new tools launch every week, existing ones get major updates, and it's hard to know which ones are worth your time and money.
      </p>
      <p>
        We cut through the hype and provide honest, practical, and beginner-friendly guides. No jargon. No fluff. Just clear, actionable advice you can use today.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Cover</h2>
      <p>
        Our content focuses on the AI tools that matter most in 2026:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>ChatGPT &amp; OpenAI tools</strong> — from basic usage to advanced workflows</li>
        <li><strong>Claude by Anthropic</strong> — when to use it, how it compares, and best practices</li>
        <li><strong>AI image generators</strong> — Midjourney, DALL-E, Stable Diffusion guides</li>
        <li><strong>Prompt engineering</strong> — techniques to get better results from any AI</li>
        <li><strong>AI tool comparisons</strong> — head-to-head reviews to help you choose</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <p>
        Every article we publish follows three principles:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Honesty first.</strong> If a tool isn't worth your time, we'll tell you. If a competitor is better, we'll say so.</li>
        <li><strong>Practical over theoretical.</strong> We focus on real-world use cases, not academic discussions.</li>
        <li><strong>Accessible to everyone.</strong> You don't need a PhD in machine learning to use AI tools effectively.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Who We Are</h2>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-6 not-prose mb-6">
        <img
          src="/avatar-256.jpg"
          srcset="/avatar-256.jpg 256w, /avatar-512.jpg 512w, /avatar-1024.jpg 1024w"
          sizes="(max-width: 768px) 96px, 128px"
          alt="Peng Zhou, founder of AI Kit Guides"
          width="128"
          height="128"
          loading="lazy"
          class="rounded-full shadow-md flex-shrink-0"
          style="width: 128px; height: 128px;"
        />
        <div class="flex-1">
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 mb-1">Peng Zhou</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-500 mb-3">Senior Java Engineer · Founder of AI Kit Guides</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        Hi, I'm Peng Zhou. I'm a senior Java engineer who's been building software for over a decade — and like a lot of developers, I got curious when ChatGPT launched in late 2022. By early 2023, I was using it every day: drafting emails, debugging tricky code, and experimenting with API integrations that actually made my work faster.
      </p>
      <p>
        Since then, AI tools have become a regular part of my workflow. Claude for code review, Midjourney for side project assets, and a growing list of smaller tools that each solve one specific problem well. I built this blog to document what I learn, in plain language, for people who want to use AI without needing a machine learning degree.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm not affiliated with any AI company. My reviews come from actually using the tools to build real things. Sometimes that means the tool works great. Sometimes it means I wasted three hours on a feature that didn't work as advertised — and I'll tell you about both.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can find me on <a href="https://github.com/zhoupeng20188" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-coral-600 hover:text-coral-700 underline">GitHub</a>, where I share code from my experiments with AI APIs and automation workflows. If you have a question or a tool you think I should check out, reach out via the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> — I read every message.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have a question, suggestion, or just want to say hi? We'd love to hear from you. Visit our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> to reach out.
      </p>
      <p>
        Subscribe to our <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a> for the latest updates.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
